==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Navelwort
<hw>Na"vel*wort`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A European perennial succulent herb (<spn>Cotyledon
umbilicus</spn>), having round, peltate leaves with a central
depression; -- also called <altname>pennywort</altname>, and
<altname>kidneywort</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Navew</ent>⟦br⟧
